66 In any trial of certain actions against a person other than the employer or a
67 person in the same employ, existing law requires that the jury must receive: (1)
68 proof of the amount of all payments made or to be made by the insurer or
69 Administrator; and (2) certain instructions from the court. (NRS 616C.215) This
70 bill removes those requirements and instead prohibits the jury from receiving proof
71 of any such payments. This bill provides that evidence of the amount of
72 compensation, accident benefits and other expenditures which the insurer or certain
73 accounts under control of the Administrator have paid or become obligated to pay
74 is not admissible at trial.
